<item>
            <title>[HBASE-746] Batching row mutations via thrift</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-746</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to be able to send to thrift a whole bunch of rows and mutations to be applied to them. This will be very useful when doing a large initial dump to HBase as doing the serialization for each row separately is expensive.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
